perl-txt2html
-------------------------------------------
Perl script and module that converts plain text to HTML. It supports 
headings, lists, simple character markup, and hyperlinking, and is 
highly customizable.  It recognizes some of the apparent structure of 
the source documents and attempts to mark that structure explicitly 
using HTML.

Runtime requirements:
  perl-5.10.0-3
  perl-Getopt-ArgvFile-1.11-1
  perl-YAML-Syck-1.04-1

Build requirements:
  cygport-0.3.9-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://txt2html.sourceforge.net/
  http://search.cpan.org/~rubykat/txt2html/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/txt2html/
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/R/RU/RUBYKAT/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-txt2html-2.51-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-txt2html-2.51-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-txt2html-2.51-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-txt2html-2.51-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/txt2html
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.10/HTML/TextToHTML.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.10/i686-cygwin/auto/HTML/TextToHTML/.packlist
  /usr/share/doc/perl-txt2html-2.51/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/perl-txt2html-2.51/README
  /usr/share/doc/perl-txt2html-2.51/TODO
  /usr/share/man/man1/txt2html.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man3/HTML.TextToHTML.3pm.gz

------------------

